lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4767  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 7a,b: Pyramidal neurons that overexpressed WT AGAP1 had significantly lower dendritic spine density, with an average 40% reduction. On the other hand, siRNA-mediated AGAP1 knockdown caused a change in spine density that did not reach statistical significance.\n\nFigure 7c,d: Spine length and neck size were significantly increased by either up or down regulation of AGAP1. Both siRNA-mediated AGAP1 knockdown and AGAP1 overexpression altered the proportions of spine types from predominately mushroom spines to primarily immature spines (Figure 7D). The proportion of thin spines increased to ~60% after AGAP knockdown.\n\n\"These data demonstrate that AGAP1 levels modulate both dendritic spine density and the proportion of morphological spine types in hippocampal pyramidal neurons.\". Experimental description: \"Hippocampal neurons were cultured form embryonic day (E) 18 Sprague-Dawley rat embryos dissected from pregnant rats\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-04" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4767" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

